## âœ¨ Why styro?

**styro** brings modern package management to the OpenFOAM ecosystem, making it easy to discover, install, and manage community-contributed packages. Whether you're a researcher, engineer, and/or developer, **styro** streamlines your workflow by eliminating manual compilation and dependency management.

### ğŸ¯ Key benefits

- **ğŸš€ One-command installation** - Install OpenFOAM packages with a single command
- **ğŸŒ Community-driven** - Access packages from the [OpenFOAM Package Index (OPI)](https://github.com/exasim-project/opi)
- **ğŸ§© Broad compatibility** - Works seamlessly with OpenFOAM from [openfoam.com](https://www.openfoam.com) and [openfoam.org](https://www.openfoam.org)
- **ğŸ“¦ Multiple sources** - Install from OPI, local directories, or Git repositories
- **ğŸ”„ Easy updates** - Upgrade packages with automatic dependency resolution
- **ğŸ› ï¸ Developer-friendly** - Simple package testing, definition and distribution


